verbose_text: A deubiquitinating enzyme cylindromatosis that inhibits NF-kappaB signaling via deubiquitination and inactivation of tumor necrosis factor receptor (TNFR)-associated factor 2 (TRAF2) and TRAF6 17 has been reported to promote inflammatory responses via mitogen activated protein kinase (MAPK)-mediated but NF-kappaB independent pathways 18.
evidence: NF-kappaB signaling via deubiquitination and inactivation of tumor necrosis factor receptor
